-- Rangers Down Capitals as Bruins Beat Maple Leafs in NHL Playoffs
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2013-05-07T02:11:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-07/rangers-down-capitals-as-bruins-beat-maple-leafs-in-nhl-playoffs.html
The  New York Rangers  beat the
Washington Capitals 4-3 to trail two games to one in their
National Hockey League playoff series.  Earlier, the Boston Bruins beat the host Toronto Maple
Leafs 5-2 to lead their best-of-seven series by two games to
one.   New York  and Toronto host Game 4 in the series on May 8.  Also tonight, Anaheim visits Detroit with the Red Wings
trailing the Ducks by two games to one, while the Los Angeles
Kings are chasing a home win to tie their series with the St.
Louis Blues at two games each.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  